# DevFlow ephemeral working state (review caches, weekly-loop temp files).
# Ignore everything under .devflow/ EXCEPT the committed overrides/templates
# below. (Use /.devflow/* — not /.devflow/ — so the negations can re-include;
# a wholesale dir-ignore can't be overridden per-path.)
/.devflow/*
!/.devflow/learnings/
# Per-run /devflow:review-and-fix effectiveness records (one file per run).
# Tracked so the data survives ephemeral GH-runner teardown — see
# docs/efficiency-trace.md. In adopter repos the scaffolder's .devflow/.gitignore
# ignores only tmp/, so logs/ is tracked there without this negation.
!/.devflow/logs/
# Committed config template + schema (shipped). The LIVE .devflow/config.json is
# NOT re-included by a negation below, so the /.devflow/* rule above would ignore a
# fresh one — but this repo TRACKS its config.json anyway: it was force-added with
# `git add -f` (a tracked file overrides .gitignore) to dogfood DevFlow on this very
# repo and have its cloud workflows read it from the committed tree. Adopters don't
# need the force-add: the scaffolder's .devflow/.gitignore ignores only tmp/, so
# their config.json (it holds project/board IDs) is tracked there too.
!/.devflow/config.example.json
!/.devflow/config.schema.json
# Shipped per-language tool/preset registry read by scripts/detect-project-tools.sh
# (/devflow:init). Must be tracked so the plugin ships it and a clean checkout works.
!/.devflow/tool-presets.json
# DevFlow's own consumer prompt extensions (e.g. the dogfooded versioning rule in
# implement.md). Tracked so a clean checkout — and CI — sees the re-homed policy.
!/.devflow/prompt-extensions/
/.devflow-scratch/
/.devflow-tmp/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
*.swp
# WSL/Windows download marker (alternate data stream) — appears on any file.
*:Zone.Identifier

# Private maintainer working docs — never publish (kept outside the repo).
/devflow-roadmap.md
*.private.md
